Step 1. Calculate Return on Equity (ROE):
• For ROE we use the net profit relative to the average owner’s equity.
• Beginning owner’s equity = 16,000,000.00  
• Ending owner’s equity = 16,111,731.83  
• Average owner’s equity = (16,000,000.00 + 16,111,731.83) / 2  
  = 32,111,731.83 / 2  
  ≈ 16,055,865.92  
• Net profit from the income statement = 111,731.83  
• ROE = (111,731.83 / 16,055,865.92) ≈ 0.006956 which is about 0.70%

Step 2. Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio:
• Total assets (end) = 19,501,451.49  
• Total liabilities can be derived as: Total Liabilities = Total Assets – Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 19,501,451.49 – 16,111,731.83  
  = 3,389,719.66  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 3,389,719.66 / 19,501,451.49 ≈ 0.1737, or about 0.17

Step 3. Calculate Gross Profit Margin:
• Gross Profit = 287,062.51 (from income statement)  
• Total Revenue = 791,992.51  
• Gross Profit Margin = 287,062.51 / 791,992.51 ≈ 0.3626, or about 36.26%

Thus, the final answers are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "0.70%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.17",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "36.26%"
  }
}
